hylloxera to help fight the grapevine phylloxera (Daktulosphaira vitifoliae) that was destroying grapevines in France. The United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) initiated research in classical biological control following the establishment of the Division of Entomology in 1881, with C. V. Riley as Chief. The first importation of a parasitoidal wasp into the United States was that of the braconid Cotesia glomerata in 1883\u20131884, imported from Europe to control the invasive cabbage white butterfly, Pieris rapae. In 1888\u20131889 the vedalia beetle, Rodolia cardinalis, a lady beetle, was introduced from Australia to California to control the cottony cushion scale, Icerya purchasi. This had become a major problem for the newly developed citrus industry in California, but by the end of 1889 the cottony cushion scale population had already declined. This great success led to further introductions of beneficial insects into the USA.	Newsletter (http://probioticdi.xyz/clk.0_14804_20877_269610_3933_7734_0300_98615fce)The diet seemed to be working...Cody was already down 15 pounds...And his Sister-in-Law was losing weight too.Things seemed to be going great...But then he got the call...His sister-in-law was in the hospital...And the doctor told Cody that he was next. (http://probioticdi.xyz/clk.2_14804_20877_269610_3933_7734_0300_dbcf9add) (http://probioticdi.xyz/clk.2_14804_20877_269610_3933_7734_0300_dbcf9add)Well even though it was one of the scariest moments of his life...This near-brush with death motivated Cody to look for a better way...And after more than two years of intensive research...Ultimately he discovered a powerful gut-restoring breakthrough... (http://probioticdi.xyz/clk.2_14804_20877_269610_3933_7734_0300_dbcf9add)Something that not only helped him to lose several pounds of unwanted body fat...But that also improved his digestion, his mood, and his energy too.Now more than 14,400 people have used Cody&#39;s discovery to quickly get the body of